Pull request successfully merged into master.

Build succeeded:
  * [Build](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/13359480742/job/37306886536)
  * [Lint style](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/13359480742/job/37306886652)

It seems this would be more consistent with the current mathlib practice:
```suggestion
namespace commGrpTypeEquivalenceCommGrp
```

I'm not sure that this would be good idea, because then the definition `inverse` in this namespace would clash with the `inverse` field of the equivalence that is defined below.

If you prefer, I can rename the namespace to `CommGrpTypeEquivalenceCommGrpAux`, but none of the other analogous constructions for monoid objects, commutative objects and group objects do this, so I would rename them all.
Ok, let us keep it like this.
